[{"id":"VR731708","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">A technology company has <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1,200\"><math alttext=\"1,200\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mtext>,</mtext><mn>200</mn></math></span></span>&nbsp;employees. The director of human resources at the company selects <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"250\"><math alttext=\"250\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>250</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>&nbsp;of the employees at random, without replacement, and asks them to fill out an anonymous survey asking whether they plan to attend the company’s holiday party. The proportion of employees in the sample who plan to attend the party is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.816\"><math alttext=\"0.816\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.816</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Based on this proportion, the director calculates a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"95\"><math alttext=\"95\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>95</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>&nbsp;percent confidence interval for the proportion of all employees who plan to attend the holiday party as  <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.816 plus or minus 1.96 times the square root of, the fraction with numerator, 0.816 times open parenthesis, 1 minus 0.816, close parenthesis, and denominator 250, end root\"><math alttext=\"0.816 plus or minus 1.96 times the square root of, the fraction with numerator, 0.816 times open parenthesis, 1 minus 0.816, close parenthesis, and denominator 250, end root\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.816</mn><mo>±</mo><mn>1.96</mn><msqrt><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.816</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>0.816</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>250</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></msqrt></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following is true concerning whether it is appropriate to use the confidence interval to estimate the proportion of all employees who plan to attend the holiday party?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR731708_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval is appropriate to use because the employees were randomly selected.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval is <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">not</span> appropriate to use because one of the values <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n times p hat\"><math alttext=\"n times p hat\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mover><mi>p</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n times open parenthesis, 1 minus p hat, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"n times open parenthesis, 1 minus p hat, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>p</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> is less than than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10\"><math alttext=\"10\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval is <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">not</span> appropriate to use because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"250\"><math alttext=\"250\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>250</mn></math></span></span> employees is more than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10%\"><math alttext=\"10%\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span></span> of all employees at the company.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval is appropriate to use because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n times p hat\"><math alttext=\"n times p hat\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mover><mi>p</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n times open parenthesis, 1 minus p hat, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"n times open parenthesis, 1 minus p hat, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>p</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> are greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10\"><math alttext=\"10\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval is appropriate to use because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n is greater than 30\"><math alttext=\"n is greater than 30\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>30</mn></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":2}]